      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are HTML Entities?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "HTML entities are used to display reserved characters and special symbols in HTML. These characters cannot be typed directly because they are part of HTML syntax."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "&entity_name;  or  &#entity_number;"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Entities"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Character", "Entity Name", "Entity Number"],
        "rows": [
          ["<", "&lt;", "&#60;"],
          [">", "&gt;", "&#62;"],
          ["&", "&amp;", "&#38;"],
          ["\"", "&quot;", "&#34;"],
          ["'", "&apos;", "&#39;"],
          [" ", "&nbsp;", "&#160;"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example Usage"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<p>5 &lt; 10</p>\n<p>Tom &amp; Jerry</p>\n<p>Use &quot;quotes&quot; here</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Non-Breaking Space"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "&nbsp; is used to add extra spaces that do not break into a new line."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
